{{Infobox person | name = Olivia Wayne | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_name = Olivia Godfrey | birth_date = {{birth year and age|1986}} | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | nationality = British | residence = [[Mill Hill]], London, England | education = | alma mater = [[University of Birmingham]] | occupation = Television sports journalist | known for = presenter on the [[Sky Sports]] television show ''[[Good Morning Sports Fans]]'' | spouse = Zeb Wayne | children = | parents = | relations = [[Jeff Wayne]] (father-in-law) | website = }}
'''Olivia Wayne''' (née Godfrey, born 1986) is a British sports journalist, and co-presenter on the [[Sky Sports]] television show ''[[Good Morning Sports Fans]]''.
==Early life== She grew up in [[Mill Hill]], London, the daughter of Jewish parents.<ref name="auto">{{cite web|title=Sky's the limit for sport presenter|url=https://www.jewishtelegraph.com/prof_363.html|work=[[Jewish Telegraph]]|first=Alex|last=Harris|accessdate=11 December 2017}}</ref> She was educated at [[North London Collegiate School]]<ref>{{citenews|title=Old North Londers — ONL Profiles: Olivia Wayne|url=http://www.nlcs.org.uk/old-north-londoners/onl-profiles/olivia-wayne|publisher=[[North London Collegiate School]]}}</ref> and earned a degree in American and Canadian studies from the [[University of Birmingham]].<ref name="auto"/><ref name="thelifestyleedit.com">{{cite web|url=http://www.thelifestyleedit.com/olivia-wayne-sky-sports-news-presenter/|title=Working Hard Pays And Sky Sports Presenter Olivia Wayne Can Prove It|date=11 May 2015|website=thelifestyleedit.com|accessdate=11 December 2017}}</ref>
==Career== She is a presenter on the [[Sky Sports]] television show ''[[Good Morning Sports Fans]]''.<ref name="auto"/><ref name="thelifestyleedit.com"/>
==Personal life== Wayne is married to DJ and producer Zeb Wayne, the son of composer and musician [[Jeff Wayne]], best known for the musical ''[[Jeff Wayne's Musical Version of The War of the Worlds|War of the Worlds]]''.<ref name="auto"/>
